        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 23 at 8:02PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 801 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 12 miles northeast of Greenwood to 11 miles
northwest of Abbeville. Movement was northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Coronaca, Cross Hill, Ware Shoals, Lake Greenwood, Cokesbury,
Mountville, Kinards, Waterloo, Hodges, and Donalds.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
